GG - Remaining CPU time

int quantum = ZZ.WW(current->HH);      // Get time slice for this priority level
current->GG -= quantum;                 // Decrease GG by time quantum
if (current->GG < 0)
    current->GG = 0;                    // Prevent negative values


HH - Priority level (0, 1, 2)
Time Quantum (2, 4, 6) 

FF - Total CPU time needed.


AA - Process Type
BB - Process State

DD - Process ID
EE - Scheduling Priority
II - Aging Counter
JJ - Current process state
KK - Max Resource needed
MM - Remaining Resources needed

OO - Resource manager tracking
PP - Request resources
QQ - Release Resources
RR - checks blocked processes
SS - Prints available resources

TT - MLFQ Scheduler
YY - Converts AA enum to queue index
OO - Enqueue new process at level 0
UU - Re queue
XX - De queue
VV - Age to promote processes
WW - Get Quantum time